.TH "TEMPORAL.PLAINMONTHDAY.TOPLAINDATE" "3JS" "December 8, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Temporal.PlainMonthDay.toPlainDate \-
Temporal.PlainMonthDay.prototype.toPlainDate()
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]toPlainDate()\f[B]\f[R] method of
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainMonthDay\f[R] instances returns a new
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainDate\f[R] object representing this month\-day and a
supplied year in the same calendar system.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
toPlainDate(yearInfo)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]yearInfo\f[R]
An object representing the year component of the resulting
\f[CR]PlainDate\f[R], containing the following properties (in the order
they are retrieved and validated):
.RS
.TP
\f[B]era\f[R] and \f[B]eraYear\f[R]
A string and an integer that correspond to the \f[CR]era\f[R] and
\f[CR]eraYear\f[R] properties.
Are only used if the calendar system has eras.
\f[CR]era\f[R] and \f[CR]eraYear\f[R] must be provided simultaneously.
If they are not provided, then \f[CR]year\f[R] must be provided.
If all of \f[CR]era\f[R], \f[CR]eraYear\f[R], and \f[CR]year\f[R] are
provided, they must be consistent.
.TP
\f[B]year\f[R]
Corresponds to the \f[CR]year\f[R] property.
.RE
.SS Return value
A new \f[CR]Temporal.PlainDate\f[R] object representing the date
specified by this month\-day and the year in \f[CR]yearInfo\f[R],
interpreted in the calendar system of this month\-day.
.SS Exceptions
.TP
\f[B]RangeError\f[R]
Thrown if any of the options is invalid.
.TP
\f[B]TypeError\f[R]
Thrown if \f[CR]yearInfo\f[R] is not an object.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Using toPlainDate()
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] md = Temporal.PlainMonthDay.from(\(dq07\-01\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] date = md.toPlainDate({ year: 2021 });
console.log(date.toString()); \f[I]// 2021\-07\-01\f[R]

\f[B]const\f[R] md2 = Temporal.PlainMonthDay.from(\(dq2021\-07\-01[u\-ca=japanese]\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] date2 = md2.toPlainDate({ era: \(dqreiwa\(dq, eraYear: 1 });
console.log(date2.toString()); \f[I]// 2019\-07\-01[u\-ca=japanese]\f[R]
.EE
